\begin_layout Section
GMM Moment Conditions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The identification strategy can be expressed more generally using GMM.
 The core idea is to form moment conditions that are zero at the true parameter values 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Triangular system
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The parameter vector is 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=(\beta_{1}',\gamma_{1},\beta_{2}')'$
\end_inset

.
 The moment vector is formed by multiplying instruments by the model's structural errors,
 which are defined as 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{1}(\theta)=Y_{1}-X'\beta_{1}-Y_{2}\gamma_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{2}(\theta)=Y_{2}-X'\beta_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
Q_{\text{TRI}}(\theta)=\begin{pmatrix}X\cdot\varepsilon_{1}(\theta)\\[3pt]
X\cdot\varepsilon_{2}(\theta)\\[3pt]
Z\cdot\varepsilon_{1}(\theta)\cdot\varepsilon_{2}(\theta)
\end{pmatrix}.\label{eq:moment_tri}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

The instruments are constructed directly from the exogenous data:
 
\end_layout

