\begin_layout Subsection
Conditional heteroscedasticity (Prono)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Context and Model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a time-series setting,
 the structural model is a triangular system:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
Y_{1t} & =X_{t}'\beta_{1}+\gamma_{1}Y_{2t}+\varepsilon_{1t}\\
Y_{2t} & =X_{t}'\beta_{2}+\varepsilon_{2t}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

The key insight is that the error variance may be time-varying and predictable.
 Prono's extension assumes 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{2t}$
\end_inset

 follows a GARCH process,
 where its conditional variance is a function of past errors and variances:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\var(\varepsilon_{2t}\mid\mathcal{F}_{t-1})=\sigma_{2t}^{2}=\omega+\alpha\varepsilon_{2,t-1}^{2}+\beta\sigma_{2,t-1}^{2}.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Procedure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The fitted conditional variance from the GARCH model serves as the heteroscedasticity driver.
 
\end_layout

