\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Context and Model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This extension formalizes identification within a GMM framework for a stationary and mixing time series.
 The structural model is a simultaneous system:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
Y_{1t} & =X_{t}'\beta_{1}+\gamma_{1}Y_{2t}+\varepsilon_{1t}\\
Y_{2t} & =X_{t}'\beta_{2}+\gamma_{2}Y_{1t}+\varepsilon_{2t}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

The key assumption is that the conditional variances are an explicit log-linear function of the exogenous variables 
\begin_inset Formula $X_{t}$
\end_inset

:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\log\sigma_{jt}^{2}=X_{t}'\delta_{j},\quad\text{where}\quad\varepsilon_{jt}\mid\mathcal{F}_{t-1}\sim(0,\sigma_{jt}^{2})\quad\text{for }j=1,2.
